{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"I thought I'd tell you a little about what I like to write."},{"time":4000,"text":"And I like to immerse myself in my topics."},{"time":8000,"text":"I just like to dive right in and become sort of a human guinea pig."},{"time":13000,"text":"And I see my life as a series of experiments."}]},{"cues":[{"time":18000,"text":"So, I work for Esquire magazine, and a couple of years ago,"},{"time":22000,"text":"I wrote an article called \"My Outsourced Life,\""},{"time":25000,"text":"where I hired a team of people in Bangalore, India,"},{"time":29000,"text":"to live my life for me."},{"time":31000,"text":"So, they answered my emails."},{"time":33000,"text":"They answered my phone."},{"time":35000,"text":"They argued with my wife for me, and they read my son bedtime stories."},{"time":42000,"text":"It was the best month of my life,"},{"time":44000,"text":"because I just sat back and I read books and watched movies."},{"time":49000,"text":"It was a wonderful experience."}]},{"cues":[{"time":51000,"text":"More recently, I wrote an article for Esquire called --"},{"time":54000,"text":"about radical honesty."},{"time":57000,"text":"And this is a movement where --"},{"time":59000,"text":"this is started by a psychologist in Virginia,"},{"time":63000,"text":"who says that you should never, ever lie,"},{"time":66000,"text":"except maybe during poker and golf, his only exceptions."},{"time":71000,"text":"And, more than that, whatever is on your brain"},{"time":73000,"text":"should come out of your mouth."},{"time":75000,"text":"So, I decided I would try this for a month."},{"time":78000,"text":"This was the worst month of my life."},{"time":81000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":82000,"text":"I do not recommend this at all."},{"time":84000,"text":"To give you a sense of the experience,"},{"time":86000,"text":"the article was called, \"I Think You're Fat.\""},{"time":90000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":92000,"text":"So, that was hard."}]},{"cues":[{"time":94000,"text":"My most recent book -- my previous book was called \"The Know-It-All,\""},{"time":99000,"text":"and it was about the year I spent reading the Encyclopedia Britannica"},{"time":103000,"text":"from A to Z in my quest to learn everything in the world,"},{"time":107000,"text":"or more precisely from Aak, which is a type of East Asian music,"},{"time":112000,"text":"all the way to Zwyiec, which is -- well, I don't want to ruin the ending."},{"time":116000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":117000,"text":"It's a very exciting twist ending, like an O. Henry novel, so I won't ruin it."},{"time":121000,"text":"But I love that one,"},{"time":123000,"text":"because that was an experiment about how much information"},{"time":127000,"text":"one human brain could absorb."},{"time":129000,"text":"Although, listening to Kevin Kelly, you don't have to remember anything."},{"time":133000,"text":"You can just Google it."},{"time":135000,"text":"So, I wasted some time there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":137000,"text":"I love those experiments,"},{"time":140000,"text":"but I think that the most profound"},{"time":142000,"text":"and life-changing experiment that I've done"},{"time":146000,"text":"is my most recent experiment, where I spent a year"},{"time":150000,"text":"trying to follow all of the rules of the Bible,"},{"time":153000,"text":"\"The Year of Living Biblically.\""},{"time":156000,"text":"And I undertook this for two reasons."},{"time":159000,"text":"The first was that I grew up with no religion at all."},{"time":163000,"text":"As I say in my book, I'm Jewish in the same way"},{"time":167000,"text":"the Olive Garden is Italian."},{"time":169000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":171000,"text":"So, not very."},{"time":173000,"text":"But I've become increasingly interested in religion."},{"time":176000,"text":"I do think it's the defining issue of our time,"},{"time":178000,"text":"or one of the main ones."},{"time":180000,"text":"And I have a son. I want to know what to teach him."},{"time":183000,"text":"So, I decided to dive in head first, and try to live the Bible."}]},{"cues":[{"time":188000,"text":"The second reason I undertook this is because"},{"time":191000,"text":"I'm concerned about the rise of fundamentalism,"},{"time":194000,"text":"religious fundamentalism, and people who say"},{"time":197000,"text":"they take the Bible literally, which is, according to some polls,"},{"time":200000,"text":"as high as 45 or 50 percent of America."},{"time":204000,"text":"So I decided, what if you really did take the Bible literally?"},{"time":208000,"text":"I decided to take it to its logical conclusion"},{"time":212000,"text":"and take everything in the Bible literally,"},{"time":214000,"text":"without picking and choosing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":217000,"text":"The first thing I did was I got a stack of bibles."},{"time":220000,"text":"I had Christian bibles."},{"time":222000,"text":"I had Jewish bibles."},{"time":224000,"text":"A friend of mine sent me something called a hip-hop bible,"},{"time":227000,"text":"where the twenty-third Psalm is rendered as, \"The Lord is all that,\""},{"time":231000,"text":"as opposed to what I knew it as, \"The Lord is my shepherd.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":235000,"text":"Then I went down and I read several versions,"},{"time":239000,"text":"and I wrote down every single law that I could find."},{"time":242000,"text":"And this was a very long list -- over 700 rules."},{"time":247000,"text":"And they range from the famous ones that I had heard of --"},{"time":250000,"text":"The Ten Commandments, love your neighbor, be fruitful and multiply."},{"time":253000,"text":"So I wanted to follow those."},{"time":255000,"text":"And actually, I take my projects very seriously,"},{"time":258000,"text":"because I had twins during my year,"},{"time":260000,"text":"so I definitely take my projects seriously."}]},{"cues":[{"time":263000,"text":"But I also wanted to follow the hundreds"},{"time":266000,"text":"of arcane and obscure laws that are in the Bible."},{"time":269000,"text":"There is the law in Leviticus,"},{"time":271000,"text":"\"You cannot shave the corners of your beard.\""},{"time":273000,"text":"I didn't know where my corners were,"},{"time":275000,"text":"so I decided to let the whole thing grow,"},{"time":278000,"text":"and this is what I looked like by the end."},{"time":281000,"text":"As you can imagine, I spent a lot of time at airport security."},{"time":285000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":287000,"text":"My wife wouldn't kiss me for the last two months."},{"time":290000,"text":"So, certainly the challenge was there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":292000,"text":"The Bible says you cannot wear clothes made of mixed fibers,"},{"time":297000,"text":"so I thought, \"Sounds strange, but I'll try it.\""},{"time":299000,"text":"You only know if you try it."},{"time":301000,"text":"I got rid of all my poly-cotton T-shirts."},{"time":304000,"text":"The Bible says that if two men are in a fight,"},{"time":308000,"text":"and the wife of one of those men grabs the testicles of the other man,"},{"time":314000,"text":"then her hand shall be cut off."},{"time":316000,"text":"So, I wanted to follow that rule."},{"time":318000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":319000,"text":"That one I followed by default,"},{"time":322000,"text":"by not getting in a fight with a man whose wife was standing nearby,"},{"time":326000,"text":"looking like she had a strong grip."},{"time":329000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":332000,"text":"So -- oh, there's another shot of my beard."}]},{"cues":[{"time":336000,"text":"I will say it was an amazing year"},{"time":338000,"text":"because it really was life changing, and incredibly challenging."},{"time":341000,"text":"And there were two types of laws that were particularly challenging."},{"time":344000,"text":"The first was avoiding the little sins that we all commit every day."},{"time":348000,"text":"You know, I could spend a year not killing,"},{"time":350000,"text":"but spending a year not gossiping, not coveting, not lying --"},{"time":355000,"text":"you know, I live in New York, and I work as a journalist,"},{"time":358000,"text":"so this was 75, 80 percent of my day I had to do it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":363000,"text":"But it was really interesting, because I was able to make some progress,"},{"time":368000,"text":"because I couldn't believe how much"},{"time":370000,"text":"my behavior changed my thoughts."},{"time":373000,"text":"This was one of the huge lessons of the year,"},{"time":375000,"text":"is that I almost pretended to be a better person,"},{"time":378000,"text":"and I became a little bit of a better person."},{"time":381000,"text":"So I had always thought, you know, \"You change your mind,"},{"time":386000,"text":"and you change your behavior,\" but it's often the other way around."},{"time":389000,"text":"You change your behavior, and you change your mind."},{"time":394000,"text":"So, you know, if you want to become more compassionate,"},{"time":397000,"text":"you visit sick people in the hospital,"},{"time":399000,"text":"and you will become more compassionate."},{"time":401000,"text":"You donate money to a cause,"},{"time":403000,"text":"and you become emotionally involved in that cause."},{"time":406000,"text":"So, it really was cognitive psychology --"},{"time":409000,"text":"you know, cognitive dissonance -- that I was experiencing."},{"time":412000,"text":"The Bible actually talks about cognitive psychology,"},{"time":415000,"text":"very primitive cognitive psychology."},{"time":417000,"text":"In the Proverbs, it says that if you smile, you will become happier,"},{"time":421000,"text":"which, as we know, is actually true."}]},{"cues":[{"time":424000,"text":"The second type of rule that was difficult to obey"},{"time":428000,"text":"was the rules that will get you into a little trouble"},{"time":431000,"text":"in twenty-first-century America."},{"time":434000,"text":"And perhaps the clearest example of this is stoning adulterers."},{"time":439000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":440000,"text":"But it's a big part of the Bible,"},{"time":444000,"text":"so I figured I had to address it."},{"time":447000,"text":"So, I was able to stone one adulterer."},{"time":449000,"text":"It happened -- I was in the park, and I was dressed in my biblical clothing,"},{"time":454000,"text":"so sandals and sort of a white robe,"},{"time":457000,"text":"you know, because again, the outer affects the inner."},{"time":459000,"text":"I wanted to see how dressing biblically affected my mind."},{"time":463000,"text":"And this man came up to me and he said,"},{"time":465000,"text":"\"Why are you dressed like that?\""},{"time":467000,"text":"And I explained my project,"},{"time":469000,"text":"and he said, \"Well, I am an adulterer, are you going to stone me?\""},{"time":472000,"text":"And I said, \"Well, that would be great!\""},{"time":475000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":480000,"text":"And I actually took out a handful of stones from my pocket"},{"time":485000,"text":"that I had been carrying around for weeks,"},{"time":487000,"text":"hoping for just this interaction -- and, you know, they were pebbles --"},{"time":491000,"text":"but he grabbed them out of my hand."},{"time":494000,"text":"He was actually an elderly man, mid-70s, just so you know."},{"time":497000,"text":"But he's still an adulterer, and still quite angry."},{"time":499000,"text":"He grabbed them out of my hand"},{"time":501000,"text":"and threw them at my face, and I felt that I could --"},{"time":504000,"text":"eye for an eye -- I could retaliate, and throw one back at him."}]},{"cues":[{"time":508000,"text":"So that was my experience stoning, and it did allow me"},{"time":511000,"text":"to talk about, in a more serious way, these big issues."},{"time":516000,"text":"How can the Bible be so barbaric in some places,"},{"time":520000,"text":"and yet so incredibly wise in others?"},{"time":523000,"text":"How should we view the Bible?"},{"time":525000,"text":"Should we view it, you know, as original intent,"},{"time":527000,"text":"like a sort of a Scalia version of the Bible?"},{"time":532000,"text":"How was the Bible written?"},{"time":534000,"text":"And actually, since this is a tech crowd,"},{"time":536000,"text":"I talk in the book about how the Bible actually reminds me"},{"time":540000,"text":"of the Wikipedia, because it has all of these authors and editors"},{"time":543000,"text":"over hundreds of years."},{"time":545000,"text":"And it's sort of evolved."},{"time":547000,"text":"It's not a book that was written and came down from on high."}]},{"cues":[{"time":552000,"text":"So I thought I would end by telling you"},{"time":556000,"text":"just a couple of the take-aways, the bigger lessons"},{"time":559000,"text":"that I learned from my year."},{"time":562000,"text":"The first is, thou shalt not take the Bible literally."},{"time":566000,"text":"This became very, very clear, early on."},{"time":569000,"text":"Because if you do, then you end up acting like a crazy person,"},{"time":572000,"text":"and stoning adulterers, or -- here's another example."},{"time":575000,"text":"Well, that's another. I did spend some time shepherding."},{"time":580000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":581000,"text":"It's a very relaxing vocation. I recommend it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":585000,"text":"But this one is -- the Bible says that you cannot touch women"},{"time":589000,"text":"during certain times of the month, and more than that,"},{"time":592000,"text":"you cannot sit on a seat where a menstruating woman has sat."},{"time":596000,"text":"And my wife thought this was very offensive,"},{"time":598000,"text":"so she sat in every seat in our apartment,"},{"time":600000,"text":"and I had to spend much of the year standing"},{"time":603000,"text":"until I bought my own seat and carried it around."}]},{"cues":[{"time":609000,"text":"So, you know, I met with creationists."},{"time":613000,"text":"I went to the creationists' museum."},{"time":615000,"text":"And these are the ultimate literalists."},{"time":617000,"text":"And it was fascinating, because they were not stupid people at all."},{"time":620000,"text":"I would wager that their IQ is exactly the same as the average evolutionist."},{"time":623000,"text":"It's just that their faith is so strong"},{"time":626000,"text":"in this literal interpretation of the Bible"},{"time":628000,"text":"that they distort all the data to fit their model."},{"time":633000,"text":"And they go through these amazing mental gymnastics to accomplish this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":637000,"text":"And I will say, though, the museum is gorgeous."},{"time":642000,"text":"They really did a fantastic job."},{"time":644000,"text":"If you're ever in Kentucky,"},{"time":645000,"text":"there's, you can see a movie of the flood,"},{"time":648000,"text":"and they have sprinklers in the ceiling"},{"time":650000,"text":"that will sprinkle on you during the flood scenes."},{"time":654000,"text":"So, whatever you think of creationism -- and I think it's crazy --"},{"time":657000,"text":"they did a great job."},{"time":660000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":662000,"text":"Another lesson is that thou shalt give thanks."},{"time":666000,"text":"And this one was a big lesson because I was praying,"},{"time":670000,"text":"giving these prayers of thanksgiving, which was odd for an agnostic."},{"time":674000,"text":"But I was saying thanks all the time, every day,"},{"time":678000,"text":"and I started to change my perspective."},{"time":681000,"text":"And I started to realize the hundreds of little things"},{"time":684000,"text":"that go right every day, that I didn't even notice,"},{"time":688000,"text":"that I took for granted, as opposed to focusing"},{"time":690000,"text":"on the three or four that went wrong."},{"time":694000,"text":"So, this is actually a key to happiness for me,"},{"time":697000,"text":"is to just remember when I came over here,"},{"time":699000,"text":"the car didn't flip over, and I didn't trip coming up the stairs."},{"time":703000,"text":"It's a remarkable thing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":707000,"text":"Third, that thou shall have reverence."},{"time":709000,"text":"This one was unexpected because I started the year"},{"time":712000,"text":"as an agnostic, and by the end of the year,"},{"time":714000,"text":"I became what a friend of mine calls a reverent agnostic, which I love."},{"time":719000,"text":"And I'm trying to start it as a movement."},{"time":721000,"text":"So, if anyone wants to join,"},{"time":723000,"text":"the basic idea is, whether or not there is a God,"},{"time":726000,"text":"there's something important and beautiful about the idea of sacredness,"},{"time":730000,"text":"and that our rituals can be sacred."},{"time":732000,"text":"The Sabbath can be sacred."},{"time":735000,"text":"This was one of the great things about my year, doing the Sabbath,"},{"time":738000,"text":"because I am a workaholic, so having this one day"},{"time":742000,"text":"where you cannot work, it really, that changed my life."},{"time":746000,"text":"So, this idea of sacredness, whether or not there is a God."}]},{"cues":[{"time":751000,"text":"Thou shall not stereotype."},{"time":753000,"text":"This one happened because"},{"time":755000,"text":"I spent a lot of time with various religious communities"},{"time":758000,"text":"throughout America because I wanted it to be more"},{"time":760000,"text":"than about my journey."},{"time":762000,"text":"I wanted it to be about religion in America."},{"time":765000,"text":"So, I spent time with evangelical Christians, and Hasidic Jews, and the Amish."},{"time":769000,"text":"I'm very proud because"},{"time":771000,"text":"I think I'm the only person in America"},{"time":773000,"text":"to out Bible-talk a Jehovah's Witness."},{"time":776000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":777000,"text":"After three and a half hours, he looked at his watch,"},{"time":780000,"text":"he's like, \"I gotta go.\""},{"time":782000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":784000,"text":"Oh, thank you very much."},{"time":789000,"text":"Thank you. Bless you, bless you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":791000,"text":"But it was interesting"},{"time":793000,"text":"because I had some very preconceived notions about, for instance,"},{"time":796000,"text":"evangelical Christianity, and I found that"},{"time":800000,"text":"it's such a wide and varied movement"},{"time":802000,"text":"that it is difficult to make generalizations about it."},{"time":808000,"text":"There's a group I met with called the Red Letter Christians,"},{"time":811000,"text":"and they focus on the red words in the Bible,"},{"time":814000,"text":"which are the ones that Jesus spoke."},{"time":816000,"text":"That's how they printed them in the old Bibles."},{"time":818000,"text":"And their argument is that Jesus never talked about homosexuality."},{"time":823000,"text":"They have a pamphlet that says,"},{"time":825000,"text":"\"Here's what Jesus said about homosexuality,\""},{"time":827000,"text":"and you open it up, and there's nothing in it."},{"time":830000,"text":"So, they say Jesus did talk a lot about helping the outcasts,"},{"time":836000,"text":"helping poor people."},{"time":839000,"text":"So, this was very inspiring to me."},{"time":843000,"text":"I recommend Jim Wallis and Tony Campolo."},{"time":848000,"text":"They're very inspiring leaders, even though I disagree"},{"time":852000,"text":"with much of what they say."}]},{"cues":[{"time":854000,"text":"Also, thou shalt not disregard the irrational."},{"time":857000,"text":"This one was very unexpected because, you know,"},{"time":861000,"text":"I grew up with the scientific worldview,"},{"time":864000,"text":"and I was shocked learning how much of my life"},{"time":871000,"text":"is governed by irrational forces."},{"time":874000,"text":"And the thing is, if they're not harmful,"},{"time":878000,"text":"they're not to be completely dismissed."},{"time":880000,"text":"Because I learned that -- I was thinking, I was"},{"time":884000,"text":"doing all these rituals, these biblical rituals,"},{"time":887000,"text":"separating my wool and linen, and I would ask these religious people"},{"time":891000,"text":"\"Why would the Bible possibly tell us to do this? Why would God care?\""},{"time":895000,"text":"And they said, \"We don't know,"},{"time":897000,"text":"but it's just rituals that give us meaning.\""},{"time":901000,"text":"And I would say, \"But that's crazy.\""},{"time":903000,"text":"And they would say, \"Well, what about you?"},{"time":905000,"text":"You blow out candles on top of a birthday cake."},{"time":910000,"text":"If a guy from Mars came down and saw, here's one guy"},{"time":914000,"text":"blowing out the fire on top of a cake"},{"time":918000,"text":"versus another guy not wearing clothes of mixed fabrics,"},{"time":922000,"text":"would the Martians say, 'Well, that guy, he makes sense,"},{"time":926000,"text":"but that guy's crazy?'\""},{"time":928000,"text":"So no, I think that rituals are, by nature, irrational."},{"time":933000,"text":"So the key is to choose the right rituals,"},{"time":936000,"text":"the ones that are not harmful -- but rituals by themselves"},{"time":942000,"text":"are not to be dismissed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":945000,"text":"And finally I learned that thou shall pick and choose."},{"time":949000,"text":"And this one I learned because"},{"time":951000,"text":"I tried to follow everything in the Bible."},{"time":953000,"text":"And I failed miserably."},{"time":955000,"text":"Because you can't."},{"time":957000,"text":"You have to pick and choose. And anyone who follows the Bible"},{"time":960000,"text":"is going to be picking and choosing."},{"time":962000,"text":"The key is to pick and choose the right parts."},{"time":967000,"text":"There's the phrase called cafeteria religion,"},{"time":971000,"text":"and the fundamentalists will use it in a denigrating way,"},{"time":975000,"text":"and they'll say, \"Oh, it's just cafeteria religion."},{"time":977000,"text":"You're just picking and choosing.\""},{"time":978000,"text":"But my argument is, \"What's wrong with cafeterias?\""},{"time":982000,"text":"I've had some great meals at cafeterias."},{"time":984000,"text":"I've also had some meals that make me want to dry heave."},{"time":988000,"text":"So, it's about choosing the parts of the Bible about compassion,"},{"time":992000,"text":"about tolerance, about loving your neighbor,"},{"time":995000,"text":"as opposed to the parts about homosexuality is a sin,"},{"time":1000000,"text":"or intolerance, or violence,"},{"time":1002000,"text":"which are very much in the Bible as well."},{"time":1004000,"text":"So if we are to find any meaning in this book,"},{"time":1008000,"text":"then we have to really engage it, and wrestle with it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1012000,"text":"And I thought I'd end with just a couple more."},{"time":1015000,"text":"There's me reading the Bible."},{"time":1017000,"text":"That's how I hailed taxicabs."},{"time":1019000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":1022000,"text":"Seriously, and it worked. And yes,"},{"time":1024000,"text":"that was actually a rented sheep,"},{"time":1027000,"text":"so I had to return that in the morning, but it served well for a day."},{"time":1032000,"text":"So, anyway, thank you so much for letting me speak."}]}]}